Preamble  
ZoobyTech believes in transparent source-code visibility while retaining sovereign stewardship over downstream use, modification, and redistribution. This Zooby Public License (“ZPL”) grants you access to, and limited rights in, the publicly-available portions of the Zooby Userland source code (the “Software”). All contributions and modifications must adhere to the defined Contribution Process and be submitted back to the ZoobyTech main repository for review. Unauthorized forks, derivative works, or redistribution contrary to these terms are prohibited.

---

## 1. Definitions

- **“Software”**  
  The publicly-available source code distributed under this license, including source files, scripts, documentation, and examples.

- **“Contributor”**  
  Any individual or entity that submits Contributions to the Software.

- **“Contribution”**  
  Any original work of authorship, including modifications, patches, bug fixes, improvements, documentation, or other materials submitted to ZoobyTech for inclusion in the Software.

- **“Repository”**  
  The official ZoobyTech GitHub organization and associated version control systems hosting the Software.

- **“Fork”**  
  Any copy, clone, or derivative of the Software hosted outside of the official Repository, or any public redistribution not expressly authorized by ZoobyTech.

- **“Proprietary Modules”**  
  Portions of the userland code not included in this public release, which remain the exclusive property and trade secrets of ZoobyTech.

